-- Copper Futures Climb to Records in London, New York
-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 2011-02-03T01:49:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/copper-climbs-to-records-in-london-new-york-on-manufacturing-outlook.html
Copper advanced to records in London
and  New York  as manufacturing improved from China to the U.S.,
boosting the demand outlook for the metal used in construction,
appliances and autos.  Three-month delivery copper added as much as 0.5 percent to
$9,993 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange and traded at
$9,970 at 10:47 a.m. Tokyo time.  Copper for March delivery on the Comex in New York rose as
much as 0.8 percent to an all-time high of $4.58 a pound, before
trading at $4.549.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jae Hur in Singapore at 
 jhur1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Matthew Oakley  at 
